# C-g [<>]       indent {{{2

# We lost the ability to change the level of indentation on the line.
# Because we prefer to use `C-d` and `C-t` with their readline meanings.
# So, we remap the Vim default `C-d` and `C-t`, to `C-g <` and `C-g >`.
